[start section id="20103"]

Mr. Morse is a 56-year-old male who underwent a screening colonoscopy and was found to have a low rectal polyp with pathology that came back as tubulovillous adenoma. On April 14, 2010 he underwent a transanal excision of a very low rectal polyp and the pathology showed an invasive cancer extending down to the deep margin.  Unfortunately, this is in the area of his sphincter and in order to surgically remove this he would need and APR. He has also seen Dr. Lawrence to discuss chemo and radiation however surgery was recommended. He is now here for surgical intervention of his rectal cancer. He is now here for surgical intervention. Risks, benefits, alternatives, indications, procedure, team approach and advance directives discussed with the patient and he wishes to proceed with surgery.

[end section id="20103"]

